endGcode: ;Version _2.6 of the firmware can abort the print too early if the file ends;too soon. However if the file hasn't ended yet because there are comments at ;the end of the file, it won't abort yet. Therefore we have to put at least 512;bytes at the end of the g-code so that the file is not yet finished by the;time that the motion planner gets flushed. With firmware version _3.3 this;should be fixed, so this comment wouldn't be necessary any more. Now we have;to pad this text to make precisely 512 bytes.
